==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: proenzyme
<hw>pro"en*zyme</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[.]</ety>
<fld>(Bioch.)</fld> <def>Any one of a class of proteins that are
converted, in the normal course of cellular metabolism, into one or more
active enzymes; also called <altname>zymogen</altname>. The conversion
usually is due to a specific cleavage of a peptide bond by another
enzyme, or may be due to acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proface</ent>⟦br⟧
